begin_memory_text: We talked about the coronavirus mostly and how our respective states were handling it. Also about our careers and schooling and the difficulties completing it this year due to all of the complications.
middle_memory_text: We talked about our families and how they are doing with the pandemic. She talked about her brother's upcoming wedding and how difficult it would be for her family to travel to attend due to the states' restrictions on traveling.
end_memory_text: We talked about how many siblings we had and what they did for a living. We each had a respective sister who was a hairdresser and is no longer one due to the pandemic this year.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of this week I don't have much planned. I'm kind of just waiting around to start school. I will probably just play a lot of videogames, do some reading, and doing some tasks online for money. Likely a lot of cleaning as well. Overall, it's going to be a relaxed week.
critical_positive: My partner was very easy to talk to. It was easy enough to keep the conversation going. There weren't any awkward silences and each of us contributed enough to the conversation. It was quite a lot easier than previous conversations in these studies. Given, that probably has a lot to do with my own energy levels, too.
critical_negative: I can't really say that there was any negative aspect to the conversation we had. It went well enough and the task was smooth. I did have a little trouble hearing them at times, but I'm not sure if that was just my own volume level, as it was initially low. There wasn't much of a problem at all.

begin_memory_text: We talked about school and what we were planning on doing academically in the future. We talked about graduate school, what we were applying for, and his certification.
middle_memory_text: We mostly talked about the pandemic and how we were affected by the pandemic. We also talked about whether we knew people who had covid, what we have done to avoid covid, and how covid has affected our academic plans for the future.
end_memory_text: We talked about our siblings and how our sisters were both hair stylists. We also talked about how hard it was for our sisters to find new jobs when they have been used to cutting hair for so long.
rest_of_day_open: I see myself spending most of my time with my boyfriend while studying for the GRE. I plan to cook more often in an attempt to save more money. I will likely play online games frequently when I have free time and I won't be going out at all because of the pandemic.
critical_positive: I feel like the conversation started to flow more easily when we found things we had in common with each other. We also had quite a bit in common concerning our families so that made the conversations last much longer when we talked about them as well. I also talk a lot so I felt like talking more helped my conversation partner talk more.
critical_negative: The conversation was a little hard to begin because there was a moment of awkwardness where we weren't sure what to talk about. There were several times in the conversation where we ran out of things to say and we weren't similar enough to talk about one topic for the entire conversation.
